  "prompt": "What does it feel for a male not to have a father?",
  "response": "The experience of growing up without a father can vary widely depending on individual circumstances, cultural context, and personal resilience. For some males, the absence of a father can evoke feelings of loss, confusion, or emotional emptiness. It may lead to questions about identity, self-worth, and belonging, particularly if they perceive a lack of a male role model. This absence can sometimes contribute to struggles with relationships, self-esteem, or authority figures later in life.\n\nOn the other hand, many males adapt and find strength in other supportive figures, such as mothers, grandfathers, uncles, teachers, or mentors. Some may develop a deep sense of independence and resilience as a result of their experiences. The impact of not having a father is deeply personal and can shape a person in complex ways, both positively and negatively.\n\nIt\u2019s important to note that the absence of a father doesn\u2019t define a person\u2019s worth or potential. Many individuals who grow up without a father go on to lead fulfilling lives, build strong relationships, and achieve their goals. Support systems, self-awareness, and personal growth play significant roles in shaping how this experience is navigated.",
